### 5. API Endpoints & Data Fetching

#### Tool Endpoints:
```
GET /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tools
  → Returns: { tools: ToolListItem[] }
  → Hook: useTools()
  → Lists all tools with grant/governance counts

GET /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tools/{toolId}
  → Returns: ToolDetail
  → Hook: useToolDetail(toolId)
  → Fetches tool with input_schema, output_schema, grants, policies
```

#### MCP Server Endpoints:
```
GET /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/mcp-servers
  → Returns: { servers: McpServerListItem[] }
  → Hook: useMcpServers()

POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/mcp-servers
  → Create new MCP server registration

DELETE /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/mcp-servers/{serverId}
  → Remove MCP server

POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/mcp-servers/{serverId}/discover
  → Trigger tool discovery from MCP server

POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/mcp-servers/{serverId}/sync
  → Sync tools (apply discovered changes)

POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/mcp-servers/{serverId}/authorize
  → OAuth authorization flow initiation
```

#### Provider Endpoints:
```
GET /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/providers
  → Returns: { providers: ProviderListItem[] }

POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/providers
  → Create credential provider

DELETE /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/providers/{providerId}
```

#### Account Endpoints:
```
GET /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/accounts
  → Returns: { accounts: ConnectedAccountApiResponse[] }
  → Requires Better Auth session (lazy-loaded only when accounts tab active)

POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/accounts/revoke/{accountId}
```

#### Grant Endpoints:
```
POST /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tools/{toolId}/grants
  → Create access grant

DELETE /api/workspaces/{workspaceId}/tools/{toolId}/grants/{identityId}
  → Revoke grant
```

