### 9. Key Relationships in Data Model

```
Workspace
  ├── mcp_tool (many)
  │   ├── input_schema: Record
  │   ├── output_schema?: Record  [MCP Draft Spec]
  │   ├── source_server?: mcp_server (optional)
  │   └── Relations:
  │       ├── can_use (edges to identity) → grant_count
  │       └── governs_tool (edges from policy) → governance_count
  │
  ├── mcp_server (many)
  │   ├── tools (via source_server back-reference)
  │   ├── transport: "sse" | "streamable-http"
  │   ├── auth_mode: "none" | "static_headers" | "oauth" | "provider"
  │   ├── provider?: credential_provider
  │   └── oauth_account?: connected_account
  │
  ├── credential_provider (many)
  │   ├── auth_method: "oauth2" | "api_key" | "bearer" | "basic"
  │   └── Relations:
  │       └── connected_account (via provider relation)
  │
  └── connected_account (many)
      └── identity (user)
          └── Relations:
              └── can_use (edges to tool) → grants

can_use (RELATION TABLE)
  ├── in: identity
  ├── out: mcp_tool
  └── max_calls_per_hour?: number

governs_tool (RELATION TABLE)
  ├── in: policy
  ├── out: mcp_tool
  ├── conditions?: string
  ├── max_per_call?: number
  └── max_per_day?: number
```

